  "riddle": "1. Seek the year when a coalition of merchant cities first united, marking the birth of a trading alliance known as a Hansa.\n\n2. A celebration of heritage and commerce found its hosts in cities bonded by history in 1990 — which locales welcomed the eager participants?\n\n3. Look beyond ancient walls to the elevation of two vibrant Dutch cities known for their guilds and trade: one called Deventer and the other known as Zutphen. How high do they rise above the sea?\n\n4. Count the number of temples that adorn the landscapes near these two cultural hubs you just uncovered. \n\n5. Combine the heights you discovered in clue 3 with the number of temples from clue 4. What value emerges from this sum?\n\n6. What sounds does the name of the cities from clue 2 echo? Count the vowels present in that name, revealing a hidden truth.\n\n7. Between the bustling port city known for its amber and another famed for its medieval heritage, what is the distance in driving between them?\n\n8. Take the distance you calculated in clue 7 and find the next prime number that comes after. What is this integer?\n\n9. Discover how many satellites are nominally listed within the framework of an advanced positioning system, often utilized for navigation. \n\n10. Near the top of a page discussing various distances, how many languages are mentioned that offer poetic access to the world?\n\n11. In a land known for its windmills and tulips, determine the elevation of this picturesque region. \n\n12. Finally, take your vowel count from clue 6, add it to the driving distance from clue 7, and compute the expression: (9 + 636) % 10. What single digit do you uncover?",
